1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Here's what science actually says about white blood cells.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:10,400
These tiny warriors of your body fight off infections and diseases, but there's more to the story.

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:13,200
Did you know there are different types?

4
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,000
Neutrophils, lymphocytes, monocytes—they all have unique missions.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,400
Research shows they adapt to threats, even learning from past infections.

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:21,200
Imagine that!

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:23,200
But not everything is perfect.

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:26,400
Sometimes, these cells can mistakenly attack healthy tissues.

9
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:32,000
So, white blood cells are both protectors and potential troublemakers in our immune system.

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,800
Want to dive deeper into the science?

11
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:37,200
Hit subscribe for more amazing facts!
